**📚 Reference: Other Delete Dialogs**

All other delete confirmation dialogs in the application use `type="danger"`:
- ✅ Support deletion: `type="danger"` (지원사업 삭제)
- ✅ Member deletion: `type="danger"` (회원 삭제)
- ✅ Article deletion: `type="danger"` (게시글 삭제)
- ✅ Board deletion: `type="danger"` (게시판 삭제)
- ✅ Program deletion: `type="danger"` (프로그램 삭제)
- ✅ Menu deletion: `type="danger"` (메뉴 삭제)
- ✅ Code deletion: `type="danger"` (코드 삭제)

**File deletion MUST follow the same pattern for consistency.**

**When to Use Each Type:**

- `type="danger"`: ✅ **ALWAYS** for delete operations (destructive actions)
- `type="warning"`: ✅ For non-destructive warnings (e.g., "Unsaved changes will be lost")
- `type="success"`: ✅ For success messages after create/update operations

