## ⚠️ CRITICAL: Delete Success Message Dialog Pattern

**MUST ALWAYS show success message after file deletion when:**

- ✅ File deletion API returns success (result === "00")
- ✅ File is successfully removed from server
- ✅ File list is updated in UI
- ✅ User needs feedback about operation result

**MUST implement success message dialog:**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Success message after deletion

// State for message dialog (MUST export all setters)
const [showMessageDialog, setShowMessageDialog] = useState(false);
const [messageDialogTitle, setMessageDialogTitle] = useState("");
const [messageDialogMessage, setMessageDialogMessage] = useState("");
const [messageDialogType, setMessageDialogType] = useState<"danger" | "warning" | "success">("success");

// After successful deletion
if (response.result === "00") {
  // Update file list
  setExistingFiles((prev) =>
    prev.filter(
      (f) => {
        return !(
          String(f.fileId) === String(fileId) &&
          String(f.seq) === String(seq)
        );
      },
    ),
  );

  // Show success message
  setMessageDialogTitle("삭제 완료");
  setMessageDialogMessage(
    response.message || "파일이 삭제되었습니다."
  );
  setMessageDialogType("success");
  setShowMessageDialog(true);
} else {
  // Show failure message
  setMessageDialogTitle("삭제 실패");
  setMessageDialogMessage(
    response.message || "파일 삭제에 실패했습니다."
  );
  setMessageDialogType("danger");
  setShowMessageDialog(true);
}
```

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ **NEVER** delete file silently without user feedback
- ❌ **NEVER** skip success message for file deletion
- ❌ **NEVER** use console.log instead of user-visible message
- ❌ **NEVER** forget to handle deletion failure message
- ❌ **NEVER** forget to export message dialog state setters

**Why this is CRITICAL:**

User feedback is essential for file operations:
1. ❌ Users don't know if deletion succeeded
2. ❌ Users may think operation failed if no feedback
3. ❌ Poor user experience
4. ❌ Users may try to delete again (duplicate operations)
5. ❌ No way to know if error occurred

