## 🚫 Common Mistakes to Avoid

### Mistake 1: Using number type for fileId

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
export interface FileItem {
  fileId?: number; // ❌ Precision loss for 18+ digit numbers
}

// ✅ CORRECT
export interface FileItem {
  fileId?: string | number; // ✅ Handles large numbers
}
```

### Mistake 2: Direct delete without confirmation

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<button onClick={() => deleteExistingFile(file)}>
  삭제
</button>

// ✅ CORRECT
<button onClick={() => handleDeleteFileClick(file)}>
  삭제
</button>
```

### Mistake 3: Forgetting to export state setters

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
return {
  showDeleteConfirmDialog,
  // ❌ Missing: setShowDeleteConfirmDialog
  fileToDelete,
  // ❌ Missing: setFileToDelete
};

// ✅ CORRECT
return {
  showDeleteConfirmDialog,
  setShowDeleteConfirmDialog, // ✅ Setter exported
  fileToDelete,
  setFileToDelete, // ✅ Setter exported
};
```

### Mistake 4: Direct comparison without String() conversion

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
prev.filter((f) => f.fileId === fileId) // ❌ Type mismatch

// ✅ CORRECT
prev.filter((f) => String(f.fileId) === String(fileId)) // ✅ String conversion
```

### Mistake 5: Not showing success message

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
if (response.result === "00") {
  setExistingFiles(/* ... */);
  // ❌ No success message
}

// ✅ CORRECT
if (response.result === "00") {
  setExistingFiles(/* ... */);
  setMessageDialogTitle("삭제 완료");
  setMessageDialogMessage("파일이 삭제되었습니다.");
  setMessageDialogType("success");
  setShowMessageDialog(true);
}
```

### Mistake 6: Using type="warning" for file deletion

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<ConfirmDialog
  type="warning"  // ❌ Yellow icon, inconsistent with other deletes
  title="파일 삭제"
  message="해당 파일을 삭제하시겠습니까?"
  // ...
/>

// ✅ CORRECT
<ConfirmDialog
  type="danger"  // ✅ Red icon, matches other delete dialogs
  title="파일 삭제"
  message="해당 파일을 삭제하시겠습니까?"
  // ...
/>
```

